# T5g current bridge health - 2026-05-23

Purpose: make the autonomy verifier prove current bridge health, not only
historical file-backed gauntlet evidence.

## Added verifier checks

scripts/verify-pentagon-autonomy-from-logs.mjs now requires:

- LaunchAgent readback exits 0.
- LaunchAgent state is running.
- LaunchAgent has a live pid.
- LaunchAgent is running with --max-age-seconds 180.
- LaunchAgent is running with --interval-ms 1000.
- LaunchAgent does not report last exit code = 1.

These checks close a reliability gap: a service can be technically loaded while
still advertising a stale crash exit or running with unbounded trigger age.

## Current readback

~~~text
$ launchctl print gui/501/run.pentagon.trigger-bridge
state = running
program = /opt/homebrew/bin/node
--interval-ms 1000
--limit 8
--max-age-seconds 180
runs = 3102
pid = 98524
last terminating signal = Terminated: 15
~~~

The last terminating signal came from the intentional kickstart after the T5f
resilience patch. There is no current last exit code = 1 line in the launchd
readback.

## Boundary

This is a bridge-health gate. It improves reliability of the current mitigation
but does not close the native Pentagon autonomy requirement.
